  "attachmentHtml": "\n<p><strong>PC Number: </strong>2012-0205<br></p><p><strong>Date: </strong>2012-03-01</p><hr><p>\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n\t&nbsp;\t&nbsp;His Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness, hereby \n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n\t&nbsp;(a)\t&nbsp;pursuant to section 103 of the <em>Corrections and Conditional Release Act</em>, appoints Howard M. Bruce of Québec, Quebec, to be a full-time member of the National Parole Board to hold office during good behaviour for a period of three years; and \n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n\t&nbsp;(b)\t&nbsp;pursuant to subsection 146(1) of the <em>Corrections and Conditional Release Act</em>, designates Howard M. Bruce to be a full-time member of the Appeal Division of the National Parole Board; \n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\neffective March 26, 2012.   \n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</p>\n<br style=\"page-break-before:always\">\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n\t&nbsp;\t&nbsp;Sur recommandation du ministre de la Sécurité publique et de la Protection civile, Son Excellence le Gouverneur général en conseil\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n\t&nbsp;a)\t&nbsp;en vertu de l’article 103 de la <em>Loi sur le système correctionnel et la mise en liberté sous condition</em>, nomme Howard M. Bruce, de Québec (Québec), membre à temps plein de la Commission nationale des libérations conditionnelles à titre inamovible pour un mandat de trois ans; \n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n\t&nbsp;b)\t&nbsp;en vertu du paragraphe 146(1) de la <em>Loi sur le système correctionnel et la mise en liberté sous condition</em>, choisit Howard M. Bruce, membre à temps plein de la Section d’appel de la Commission nationale des libérations conditionnelles;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\nà compter du 26 mars 2012.    \n\n</p><p style=\"margin-left:0.50in;margin-right:2.00in;text-align:justify;margin-top:0.00in;margin-bottom:0.00in;\">\n&nbsp;\n</p>\n\n<p></p><form method=\"post\" action=\"index.php\"><input type=\"submit\" value=\"Back to Form\" class=\"btn btn-primary\" name=\"return\"></form>\t\t\n        <!-- end main content -